  ${
    $d I x $.  $d Z x $.
    lidlnz.u $e |- U = ( LIdeal ` R ) $.
    lidlnz.z $e |- Z = ( 0g ` R ) $.
    $( A nonzero ideal contains a nonzero element.  (Contributed by Stefan
       O'Rear, 3-Jan-2015.) $)
    lidlnz $p |- ( ( R e. Ring /\ I e. U /\ I =/= { Z } ) ->
        E. x e. I x =/= Z ) $=
      ( crg wcel csn wne w3a cv wn wa wex wrex wpss wss lidl0cl necomd sylanbrc
